11/08/2009
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Prime Minister Emil Boc announced on Monday (August 10th) that his cabinet will ask for a vote of confidence on several bills requested by the IMF, once lawmakers return from summer recess on September 2nd. After a coalition meeting Monday, Boc said the Liberal Democratic Party and the Social Democratic Party have agreed to move quickly in parliament on the series of bills. These include the single wage bill, one that restructures government agencies, one that covers cumulative pensions, and the education bill. Boc says all these new bills will be presented to parliament in one large package. (Ziare, Mediamax - 10/08/09)
